---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro'

const handoffUrl = 'https://github.com/bigailabs/cathedral/blob/main/docs/validator.md'
const configUrl = 'https://github.com/bigailabs/cathedral/blob/main/config/cathedral-validator.toml.example'
const repoUrl = 'https://github.com/bigailabs/cathedral'
---

<Base title="validator · cathedral">
  <style>
    .eyebrow {
      font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.22em; text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--dim); display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 10px;
    }
    .eyebrow .num { font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; color: var(--accent); }
    .sec { padding: 52px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-soft); }
    .sec:last-of-type { border-bottom: 0; }
    .wrap { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 160px 1fr; gap: 48px; }
    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .sec { padding: 38px 0; }
      .wrap { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 20px; }
    }
    .lede {
      font-family: var(--font-serif, 'Newsreader', ui-serif, Georgia, serif);
      font-size: clamp(28px, 5vw, 54px);
      font-weight: 300;
      line-height: 1.02;
      color: var(--fg);
      max-width: 12ch;
      margin: 0;
    }
    .lede em { font-style: italic; color: var(--muted); }
    .copy {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 12px;
      line-height: 1.7;
      max-width: 68ch;
      margin: 18px 0 0;
    }
    .actions {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 10px;
      margin-top: 24px;
    }
    .btn {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      min-height: 38px;
      padding: 0 14px;
      border: 1px solid var(--accent);
      color: var(--fg);
      background: var(--accent-dim);
      font-size: 10px;
      letter-spacing: 0.16em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      transition: color 150ms ease, border-color 150ms ease, background 150ms ease;
    }
    .btn:hover,
    .btn:focus-visible {
      color: var(--bg);
      background: var(--accent);
      outline: 2px solid var(--accent);
      outline-offset: 2px;
    }
    .btn.secondary {
      border-color: var(--border);
      background: transparent;
      color: var(--muted);
    }
    .btn.secondary:hover,
    .btn.secondary:focus-visible {
      border-color: var(--muted);
      background: var(--surface);
      color: var(--fg);
    }
    .grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 12px;
    }
    @media (max-width: 800px) {
      .grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }
    .card {
      min-height: 172px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      background: var(--surface);
      padding: 18px 18px 16px;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 12px;
    }
    .card-k {
      color: var(--accent);
      font-size: 10px;
      letter-spacing: 0.18em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }
    .card h2 {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--fg);
      font-family: var(--font-serif, 'Newsreader', ui-serif, Georgia, serif);
      font-size: 24px;
      font-weight: 300;
      line-height: 1.16;
    }
    .card p {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 12px;
      line-height: 1.65;
    }
    .steps {
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .step {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 58px minmax(0, 1fr);
      gap: 18px;
      padding: 16px 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-soft);
    }
    .step:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
    .step .n {
      color: var(--accent);
      font-size: 11px;
      letter-spacing: 0.18em;
      font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
    }
    .step .body {
      color: var(--fg);
      font-size: 12px;
      line-height: 1.7;
    }
    .step .body code {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
      font-size: 11px;
    }
    pre.code {
      margin: 10px 0 0;
      padding: 14px 16px;
      overflow-x: auto;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      background: var(--surface);
      color: var(--fg);
      font-size: 11px;
      line-height: 1.7;
    }
    .note {
      border-left: 2px solid var(--warn);
      background: var(--warn-dim);
      color: var(--fg);
      padding: 12px 14px;
      font-size: 12px;
      line-height: 1.65;
      max-width: 72ch;
    }
    .note strong { color: var(--warn); font-weight: 500; }
    .link {
      color: var(--fg);
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-decoration-color: var(--dim);
      text-underline-offset: 3px;
    }
    .link:hover,
    .link:focus-visible {
      color: var(--accent);
      outline: none;
    }
  </style>

  <section class="sec">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div><div class="eyebrow"><span class="num">00</span><span>Validator</span></div></div>
      <div>
        <h1 class="lede">Run the SN39 validator.</h1>
        <p class="copy">
          Cathedral validators verify the work miners submit and set weights for the mechanism.
          The goal is simple: run the validator, score deployable work honestly, and help us route
          real Polaris usage back through the Bittensor ecosystem.
        </p>
        <div class="actions">
          <a class="btn" href={handoffUrl}>Open handoff</a>
          <a class="btn secondary" href={configUrl}>Config example</a>
          <a class="btn secondary" href={repoUrl}>Repository</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="sec">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div><div class="eyebrow"><span class="num">01</span><span>What you run</span></div></div>
      <div class="grid">
        <article class="card">
          <div class="card-k">Mechanism</div>
          <h2>Cathedral validator</h2>
          <p>Build from source, connect a permitted SN39 hotkey, discover miners, verify their submissions, and emit weights.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <div class="card-k">Path</div>
          <h2>Your hotkey, or child-hotkey</h2>
          <p>Run the validator from your own permitted hotkey, or child-hotkey Cathedral so we can operate the same mechanism for the experiment.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <div class="card-k">Reason</div>
          <h2>Demand-led rewards</h2>
          <p>Polaris runs jobs. Cathedral rewards deployable improvements that make those jobs cheaper, faster, or more reliable.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="sec">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div><div class="eyebrow"><span class="num">02</span><span>Quick path</span></div></div>
      <div>
        <div class="steps">
          <div class="step">
            <div class="n">01</div>
            <div class="body">
              Clone the validator repo and install the Rust build dependencies from the handoff.
<pre class="code">git clone https://github.com/bigailabs/cathedral.git
cd cathedral</pre>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="n">02</div>
            <div class="body">
              Copy the Cathedral config example and set your wallet, hotkey, network, and local paths.
<pre class="code">cp config/cathedral-validator.toml.example config/validator.toml</pre>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="n">03</div>
            <div class="body">
              Build and start the validator.
<pre class="code">cargo build --release -p basilica-validator --bin cathedral-validator
RUST_LOG=info,cathedral_validator=debug \
  ./target/release/cathedral-validator --config config/validator.toml start</pre>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="n">04</div>
            <div class="body">
              Check the local health endpoints.
<pre class="code">curl http://127.0.0.1:8080/health
curl http://127.0.0.1:8080/miners
curl http://127.0.0.1:9090/metrics</pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="copy">
          Full details live in the
          <a class="link" href={handoffUrl}>validator handoff</a>. Use that page as the source of truth.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="sec">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div><div class="eyebrow"><span class="num">03</span><span>Current reference</span></div></div>
      <div>
        <div class="note">
          <strong>Known-good path:</strong> the Cathedral operator validator is live on SN39,
          the validator API is healthy, miners are discovered, and the public log stream is clean.
          This page exists so validators can use the same source-build path without hunting through Discord.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
